\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. M. heterophyllum} Michx,{\i  Fl. Bor. Amer. }{\b 2}: 191 (1803). Stems up to 100 cm. Leaves 4-6 in a whorl, either pinnatisect, with 5-12 capillary segments, or lanceolate to linear and serrate. Spike 3-35 cm, with solitary flowers borne in the axils of lance olate bracts. Flowers hermaphrodite, or occasionally female at base of inflorescence, male above. Petals 1·5-3 mm. Stamens 4. Fruit 1-1·5 mm, subglobose, each nutlet beaked and with 2 ridges on the outer face, finely tuberculate.{\i  Naturalized in S.E. Austria.} [Au Br.] ({\i E. North America.})
\par

